page.title: 01Skiddaws Western fellside
page.content: This area is wholly within the Lake District National park. It is dominated by the fellsides of Skiddaw and includes the peak known as Skiddaw Little Man. This peak can be reached by footpath from Millbeck. To north and west the fellside is afforested with conifers and is known as Dodd wood. Some felling is at present taking place. The wood has a typical variety of flora and fauna and also has marked footpaths for walkers. The small settlements of Millbeck, Applethwaite Underscar and Ormathwaite comprise a variety of modernised homes some of whose residents work in Keswick. Other residents are engaged in tourism and agriculture . part of A591 Keswick to Carlisle road passes through this area.
